accessrestrict.head: Conditions Governing Access
accessrestrict.p: Faculty recommendations are restricted for 75 years from date of creation.

The materials are open for research use; materials must be requested at least 48 hours in advance of intended use. Audio-visual materials are not available in original format, and must be reformatted to a digital use copy.

bioghist.head: Biographical / Historical
bioghist.p: John I. Brauman earned an SB from the Massachusetts Institute of Technology in 1959, and a PhD from the University of California at Berkeley in 1963. Following a National Science Foundation Postdoctoral Fellowship at the University of California, Los Angeles, he accepted a position at Stanford University where he is now J. G. Jackson - C. J. Wood Professor of Chemistry Emeritus, and serves as Associate Dean of Research. Biographical information from: https://chemistry.stanford.edu/people/john-brauman.
